@peculiarcorpse You will all be in the same place, therefore there is nobody sicker than another person in that facility
And you never know what stage of recovery somebody is in either, so never compare yourself to the people there.

I understand the fear though. I had it too

@peculiarcorpse There is a point, omg never let that steer you away

It’s never too early or too late to start recovering.
If you have even a little part of you who wants to start trying now, do it. Believe me it’ll make your journey there so much easier, and you’ll leave sooner!

@peculiarcorpse I’m not saying you have to fully recover or do it on your own.

I’m saying, me for example. Right before I went inpatient I went out to eat for the first time in months.
It was terrifying. I cried and lost my shit and my parents had to pull over. But I do it, and it helped https://t.co/ArvuYLUr8d

@peculiarcorpse I say maintain.
I’m glad you’re getting help. It’s scary I know it is but I do think it’ll be so worth it.

Just hold out. You can even start challenging yourself a little more while you’re home to get used to what you’re going to experience, in the comfort of your home🫶
